tf_nightly_gpu-1.6.0.dev20180125-cp27-cp27mu-manylinux1_x86_64.whl )

Basically uninstalled my previously installed version. For it to work, had to also install CUDA-9.0 and cudnn7.

My codes worked for a while (usually about 50 iterations). Still SIGSEGV and get the same stack trace.
Is it helpful to mention that I use feed_dict in tf.run() to set my current batch for training.

Myself and Peiliang Li are using the same pysical computer.
